<subSubSection lastPageId="168" lastPageNumber="169" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="167" pageNumber="168">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="168" lastPageNumber="169" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">
Perennial herb, often mat-forming, from a thick, branched underground rhizome; stems ascending to 30 cm, vegetative parts densely but minutely puberulent to shiny white-sericeous. Basal leaves 4.5-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-1.8 cm, oblong to oblanceolate, acute, entire, attenuate at base into a long pseudopetiole; stem leaves distinctly sessile, 1.5-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.7 cm, narrowly linear-oblanceolate, acute. Flowers in terminal diachasial cymes and axillary cymes of 1-5 flowers; bracts and bracteoles not clearly differentiated, 
<pageBreakToken pageId="168" pageNumber="169" start="start">3</pageBreakToken>
-25 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-3 mm, linear to oblanceolate, acute, very variable in size; pedicels 3-4 mm; sepals of two parts-pale base and acute, commonly reflexed, green apex; outer sepals 6-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm, oblong-lanceolate; inner sepals 6-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm, broadly ovate, margins scarious; corolla 1.8-2.5 cm long, pink with white centre and paler midpetaline bands, shallowly lobed, midpetaline bands appressed pilose; ovary conical, sericeous, style pilose, divided 7-10 mm above base, stigmas 5-7 mm; capsule pubescent; seeds shortly pubescent. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 128; 
<bibRefCitation author="Meikle, RD" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Cyprus" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1163 - 1179" refId="B227" refString="Meikle, RD, 1985. . Flora of Cyprus volume 2: 1163 - 1179" volume="volume 2" year="1985">Meikle 1985</bibRefCitation>
: 1170; 
<bibRefCitation author="Austin, DF" editor="Nasir, E" journalOrPublisher="Dept. of Botany, University of Karachi, Karachi" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 64" refId="B13" refString="Austin, DF, Ghazanfar, S, 1979. Convolvulaceae. In: Nasir, E, Ali, SI, Eds., Flora of Pakistan 126: Convolvulaceae. Dept. of Botany, University of Karachi, Karachi: 1 - 64" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Pakistan 126: Convolvulaceae." year="1979">Austin and Ghazanfar 1979</bibRefCitation>
: 18; 
